DAN CAR GAME POLICY

Privacy Policy

Our mobile game, (Dan Car Game), values the privacy of its users. We understand that your personal and device information is important, and we are committed to protecting it. This privacy policy outlines the types of information we collect and how we use it.

Information Collection

We collect information in the following ways:

Information you provide: When you install and use our game, we may ask for certain information such as your name, email address, and device information. This information is used to enhance your experience and to provide support and technical assistance if needed.

Information collected automatically: When you use our game, we may automatically collect information about your device and usage data such as IP address, device type, operating system, and screen resolution.

Information Usage

We use the information we collect for the following purposes:

To provide and improve our game: We use the information to enhance the functionality and performance of our game and to provide a better user experience.

To personalize your experience: We use the information to personalize your experience and to provide tailored content and advertisements based on your preferences.

To communicate with you: We may use the information to communicate with you about updates, technical support, and other important information related to our game.

Information Sharing

We do not sell or share your personal information with third-party advertisers. We may share anonymous usage data with our partners to help us improve the performance and functionality of our game.

Data Retention

We retain your personal information for as long as it is necessary to provide you with our services and to comply with legal obligations.

Security

We take reasonable steps to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no method of electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee the security of your information.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or to comply with legal requirements. We will notify you of any material changes by posting the updated policy on our website.

Contact Us

If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please contact us at d_vu@fanshaweonline.ca.

Last Updated: 2023-02-11
